   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Knowledge Base Gap Detector\\n\",\"**NLP Project 89 of 100** — Find unanswered question clusters to identify gaps in knowledge base coverage.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\nfrom sklearn.cluster import KMeans\\nfrom sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nSEED = 42; rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Existing KB articles\\nkb_articles = [\\n    'How to reset your password','Payment methods we accept','Our refund policy',\\n    'How to contact support','Business hours and locations','Shipping information',\\n]\\n\\n# Incoming customer questions\\nquestions = [\\n    'How do I change my email address?','Can I pause my subscription?','Do you ship internationally?',\\n    'How to reset password','What payment do you take?','Is there a student discount?',\\n    'How to cancel my account?','Do you have a mobile app?','Can I change my plan?',\\n    'Where is my refund?','How to contact you?','Do you offer group pricing?',\\n    'API documentation?','Can I export my data?','Two-factor authentication setup?',\\n] * 5\\n\\nprint(f'KB articles: {len(kb_articles)}, Questions: {len(questions)}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Find questions NOT covered by KB\\ntfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=3000)\\nall_texts = kb_articles + questions\\nX = tfidf.fit_transform(all_texts)\\n\\nkb_embs = X[:len(kb_articles)]\\nq_embs = X[len(kb_articles):]\\n\\n# Similarity of each question to best KB article\\nsims = cosine_similarity(q_embs, kb_embs)\\nmax_sims = sims.max(axis=1)\\n\\ndf_q = pd.DataFrame({'question': questions, 'best_kb_sim': max_sims})\\ndf_q['covered'] = df_q['best_kb_sim'] > 0.3\\n\\nprint(f'Covered: {df_q[\\\"covered\\\"].sum()}/{len(df_q)}')\\nprint(f'Gap rate: {(~df_q[\\\"covered\\\"]).mean():.1%}')\\nprint(f'\\\\nUncovered questions (gaps):')\\nfor q in df_q[~df_q['covered']]['question'].unique():\\n    print(f'  ❌ {q}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Cluster gaps to find themes\\ngap_questions = df_q[~df_q['covered']]['question'].unique().tolist()\\nif len(gap_questions) >= 3:\\n    gap_tfidf = tfidf.transform(gap_questions)\\n    n_clusters = min(3, len(gap_questions))\\n    km = KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters, random_state=SEED, n_init=10)\\n    labels = km.fit_predict(gap_tfidf)\\n    terms = tfidf.get_feature_names_out()\\n    print('\\\\nGap Clusters (suggested new KB articles):')\\n    for i in range(n_clusters):\\n        top = [terms[j] for j in km.cluster_centers_[i].argsort()[-3:][::-1]]\\n        cluster_qs = [gap_questions[j] for j in range(len(gap_questions)) if labels[j]==i]\\n        print(f'  Cluster {i} (keywords: {top}): {cluster_qs[:3]}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Gap detection identifies questions not covered** by existing KB articles.\\n\",\"- **Clustering gaps reveals article topics** that should be created.\\n\",\"- **Automate weekly gap reports** to keep KB coverage high.\\n\",\"- **For production, track gap rate over time** as a KPI.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
